# =============================================================================
# global.wqmignore — daemon-wide index exclusions (template)
# =============================================================================
# Patterns here are applied to EVERY indexed project on top of each project's
# own .gitignore / .wqmignore. Uses standard gitignore syntax:
#
#   node_modules/   — exclude directory (trailing slash = dirs only)
#   *.zip           — exclude by extension
#   !important.log  — re-include a previously excluded path
#
# Anchored vs. unanchored: the Rust `ignore` crate treats patterns without a
# leading slash as matching at any depth, but `add_ignore()` (used for
# global.wqmignore) anchors them relative to the ignore-file's parent dir.
# Use the `**/` prefix when you need a pattern to match deep inside arbitrary
# project trees (see the IDE/cache sections below for examples).
#
# Changes take effect at the next ignore-file reconciliation event (triggered
# automatically when any project's .gitignore or .wqmignore is modified, or
# at the next daemon restart).
#
# Deployment: copy this file to `<daemon-state-dir>/global.wqmignore` (host
# bind-mount target for /var/lib/memexd/global.wqmignore — see docker-compose).
# For the bundled compose stack that's `state/memexd/global.wqmignore`.
# =============================================================================

# ─── Pattern syntax note ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Directory exclusion via trailing slash (`testlink/`) does NOT reliably keep
# the walker out of that subtree when the pattern lives in global.wqmignore.
# Use the explicit `/**` suffix when you want to exclude an entire subtree:
#
#   **/some/subtree/**          # exclude everything inside
#   !**/some/subtree/keep/**    # re-include a slice (needs its own /** too)
#
# This is more verbose than gitignore's `subtree/` shorthand, but matches what
# the Rust `ignore` crate's add_ignore() actually applies cross-tree.

# ─── Self-storage (Qdrant + memexd + MCP local state) ────────────────────────
# When the workspace-qdrant-mcp repo itself is registered as a project, the
# daemon would otherwise watch its own Qdrant storage / SQLite WAL / MCP logs,
# creating a feedback loop: Qdrant rotates a segment -> fs event -> enqueue
# Add/Delete -> daemon hits Qdrant -> Qdrant rotates more -> fs event -> ...
# Excluding the host-bind state dir breaks the loop.
#
# See docs/runbooks/self-watch-loop.md for the diagnosis and recovery
# procedure if you discover the loop already running.
state/
**/state/qdrant/
**/state/memexd/
**/state/mcp/
**/.fastembed_cache/

# ─── Build artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
build/
dist/
out/
target/
_build/
coverage/
**/coverage/
*.class
*.o
*.a
*.so
*.dylib
*.dll
*.exe
*.pdb

# ─── Dependency / vendor directories ─────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
vendors/
vendor/
bower_components/
jspm_packages/

# ─── Python virtual environments ─────────────────────────────────────────────
venv/
.venv/
env/
.env/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python

# ─── IDE / editor state ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Belt-and-suspenders: both anchored and **/ forms because the Rust `ignore`
# crate's add_ignore() treats patterns as anchored to the ignore-file's
# parent dir, not the walk root. Without **/ prefix, .claude/ would only
# match /home/memexd/.workspace-qdrant/.claude/ — NOT project-level .claude/.
.claude/
**/.claude/
.codex/
**/.codex/
.codex-skill-staging/
**/.codex-skill-staging/
.agents/
**/.agents/
.idea/
**/.idea/
.vscode/
**/.vscode/
*.iml
*.suo
*.ntvs_analysis.dat

# ─── Git internals (not auto-skipped when hidden=false) ──────────────────────
.git/
**/.git/

# ─── Toolchain caches ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.gradle/
**/.gradle/
.gradle-user/
**/.gradle-user/
.gradle-user-codex/
**/.gradle-user-codex/
.gradle-user-root/
**/.gradle-user-root/
.tools/
**/.tools/
.m2/
**/.m2/
.ivy2/
**/.ivy2/
.cargo/
**/.cargo/
.rustup/
**/.rustup/
.stack-work/
**/.stack-work/

# ─── Image / media assets (FastEmbed is text-only) ───────────────────────────
*.gif
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.ico
*.webp
*.svg
*.bmp
*.tiff
*.mp3
*.mp4
*.avi
*.mov
*.webm
*.wav
*.flac
*.ogg

# ─── Generated / large templates ─────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tpl

# ─── Archives and binary blobs ───────────────────────────────────────────────
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tar.bz2
*.tar.xz
*.tgz
*.gz
*.bz2
*.xz
*.7z
*.rar
*.jar
*.war
*.ear
*.iso
*.img
*.dmg

# ─── Generated / compiled assets ─────────────────────────────────────────────
*.min.js
*.min.css
*.bundle.js
*.map

# ─── Lock files (large, machine-generated) ───────────────────────────────────
# package-lock.json and pnpm-lock.yaml regularly hit 500KB-2MB and add no
# search value over the package.json source. Enabled by default; comment out
# if your workflow relies on grep over lockfile contents.
package-lock.json
pnpm-lock.yaml
yarn.lock
# Cargo.lock                # opt-in: useful for grep in Rust workspaces
# Gemfile.lock
# poetry.lock

# ─── Generated proto / gRPC stubs ────────────────────────────────────────────
# protobuf-java emits *.java under generated dirs; same files re-emerge on
# every build. Search via `grep` on these is noise — the .proto source is
# what people actually want to look at.
**/proto/src/generated/
**/*_proto/
**/generated/proto/
# protobuf-java naming convention: outer class for a .proto file gets the
# suffix OuterClass.java (e.g. Profile.proto → ProfileOuterClass.java).
# Catches anything emitted under proto/doc/, proto/api/, proto/<anywhere>/.
**/*OuterClass.java

# ─── User uploads / dump dirs ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Conventional location for uploaded artifacts (CSV dumps, file uploads,
# database exports). Skip the whole subtree — legitimate code doesn't live
# under uploads/. If you DO have code in an uploads/ dir, add a re-include
# (e.g. `!**/uploads/keep.ts`).
**/uploads/

# ─── Test result dumps ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Playwright / Jest / Cypress emit massive JSON result files that can grow
# to hundreds of MB after a few runs.
**/e2e-results*.json
**/test-results*.json
**/playwright-report/
**/validation-reports/
**/test-artifacts/
**/backend-test-artifacts/

# ─── Generated third-party license bundles ───────────────────────────────────
# `**/` prefix required: add_ignore() anchors patterns relative to the
# ignore-file's parent dir (see header comment on anchored vs. unanchored).
**/THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md
**/THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md
**/THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.txt
**/LICENSE-3rdparty.json
